id--automatic\">\r\n<div class=\" grid__column\" style=\"padding: 15px;\">\r\n<div id=\"_GNZdH1\" class=\"_PNdBOk _GNZdH1 contact-page\">\r\n<div id=\"_gbmWH0\" class=\"_RbpgL7 _gbmWH0\">{pb3loadmodule 283}</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<!-- End PageFly HTML --><!-- Start PageFly Data||End PageFly Data -->','',1,100,'2016-12-14 03:02:25',820,'','2017-12-24 01:32:59',560,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2016-12-14 03:02:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{}','{}','{\"article_layout\":\"_:default\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"sunfw_article_type\":\"standard\",\"sunfw_featured_image\":\"\",\"sunfw_audio_embed_code\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_title\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_url\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_text\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_author\":\"\",\"sunfw_video_url\":\"\"}',14,1,'','',1,1237,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(142,490,'Our Mandate','our-mandate','<div class=\"iccc-article-title\">\r\n<h3>Our Mandate</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<p>The ICCC is an independent statutory authority established in January 2003 following the enactment of the ICCC Act by the Parliment in March, 2002.</p>\r\n<p>The ICCC is responsible for promoting and safeguarding competition, protecting consumer\'s interests and regulating declared industries, entities and goods and services.</p>\r\n<p>Its primary objectives are defined and set out in Section 5 of the ICCC Act.</p>\r\n<p>These are:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n<li>To enhance the welfare of the people of Papua New Guinea through the promotion of competition, fair trading and the protection of consumer\'s interests.</li>\r\n<li>To promote economic efficiency in industry structure, investment and conduct; and</li>\r\n<li>To protect the long term interests of the people of Papua New Guinea with regard to the price,quality and reliability of significant goods and services.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Our Vision</h4>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<p>Ensure an efficient economy in which markets are competitive, consumers\' interests are protected and regulated industries are efficient.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Our Mission</h4>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<p>To enhance the welfare of the people of Papua New Guinea where:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Markets are competitive, efficient and informed;</li>\r\n<li>Consumers are effectively protected from misleading and deceptive conduct and unsafe goods;</li>\r\n<li>Regulated goods and services are delivered efficiently; and</li>\r\n<li>Our work is aligned with national development plans and strategies such as the Medium Term Development Plan, Development Strategic Plan, and Vision 2050 and conducted independently, transparently and accountably.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Our Values</h4>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<p>Our organization is committed to promote and uphold:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Independence and Accessibility - The ICCC Act ensures the independence of the ICCC. We will always be accessible to our clients and stakeholders.</li>\r\n<li>Transparency and accountability - Our communication and decisions will be made in a consultative and open manner with input by stakeholders. We will take responsibility for our decisions and conduct.</li>\r\n<li>Ethical conduct &amp; Professionalism - Our conduct will be of high standards and efficient, focused to produce quality outcomes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>','',1,95,'2017-12-19 22:11:56',560,'','2017-12-22 05:11:53',560,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2017-12-19 22:11:56','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{}','{}','{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"sunfw_article_type\":\"standard\",\"sunfw_featured_image\":\"\",\"sunfw_audio_embed_code\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_title\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_url\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_text\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_author\":\"\",\"sunfw_video_url\":\"\"}',18,5,'','',1,2021,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(143,498,'The Commissioners (The Board)','the-commissioners-the-board','<div class=\"iccc-article-title\">\r\n<h3>The Commissioners (The Board)</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"main\" style=\"overflow: auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"iccc-figure-profile the-commissioners\">\r\n<p><img class=\"iccc-figure-common-scaled\" src=\"images/iccc/photogalleries/paulus-ain-mgmt-profile.jpg\" alt=\"Paulus Ain - Commissioner &amp; Chief Executive Officer\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Paulus Ain</strong><br />Commissioner &amp;<br />Chief Executive Officer</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-figure-profile the-commissioners\">\r\n<p><img class=\"iccc-figure-common-scaled\" src=\"images/iccc/photogalleries/position-vacant-mgmt-profile.png\" alt=\"Position Vacant - Associate Commissioner (Resident)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Vacant</strong><br />Associate Commissioner<br />(Resident)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-figure-profile the-commissioners\">\r\n<p><img class=\"iccc-figure-common-scaled\" src=\"images/iccc/photogalleries/edward-willet-mgmt-profile.jpg\" alt=\"Ed Willett - Associate Commissioner (Non-Resident)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Ed Willett</strong><br />Associate Commissioner<br />(Non-Resident)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','',1,95,'2017-12-19 23:31:58',560,'','2018-03-18 06:39:58',560,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2017-12-19 23:31:58','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":null,\"image_intro_caption\":null,\"image_intro_alt\":null,\"image_fulltext\":null,\"image_fulltext_caption\":null,\"image_fulltext_alt\":null}','{}','{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"sunfw_article_type\":\"standard\",\"sunfw_featured_image\":\"\",\"sunfw_audio_embed_code\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_title\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_url\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_text\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_author\":\"\",\"sunfw_video_url\":\"\"}',31,3,'','',1,3741,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(144,500,'Prices & Productivity','prices-productivity','<div class=\"iccc-article-title\">\r\n<h3>Prices &amp; Productivity</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"main\" style=\"overflow: auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"iccc-figure-common\">\r\n<p><img alt=\"Price &amp; Productivity Division Staff - Head Office\" class=\"iccc-figure-common-scaled\" src=\"images/iccc/photogalleries/PPD.jpg\" style=\"height: 308px; width: 377px;\" /></p>\r\n<p>Price &amp; Productivity Divisional Staff - Head Office</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<p>The Commission regulates and monitors prices of basic goods and services that matters most to ordinary Papua New Guineans that are declared by the Minister for Treasury under Prices Regulation Act (PR Act). The Commission also has the added responsibility of conducting special inquiry on economic productivity of certain industry as when directed by Minister or Parliament under PART VIII of the ICCC Act.</p>\r\n<p>The Commission only regulates the prices of certain goods and services declared by the Government through the Minister for Treasury under Section 10 of the PR Act for price regulation purposes. Under Section 32A of the PR Act, the ICCC monitors the prices of these goods and services. In its role of regulating these declared goods and services, the Commission powers are very much limited to only the baskets of declared goods and services after having deregulated most of the goods and services allowing the market forces to determine the prices. These declared goods and services can be found under Declared Goods and Services with special mention on the productivity matters that the ICCC does in carrying out special and specific industry reviews subject to direction from the Government though the Minister for Treasury.</p>\r\n<p>In choosing the form of price regulation that should apply to each of these declared goods and services, the Commission is required to consider the options that are available and are identified in the PR Act such as the price control under Section 10 of the PR Act and the price monitoring under Section 32A of the PR Act. Price control would require the Commission to have regard to the provisions of Sections 20A, 20B, and 21 of the PR Act. Price monitoring on the other hand under Section 32A of the Act provides a less intrusive method for price regulation.</p>\r\n<p>Under the price monitoring approach the suppliers of declared goods and services set their own prices according to their cost drives, while the Commission monitors these price movements with some independent price comparator. If the price are moving at rate not consistent with the movement in the price comparator, the commission may recommend to the Minister for Treasury to redeclare the goods and services for direct price control.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','',1,97,'2017-12-20 07:10:20',560,'','2018-03-18 04:54:07',560,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2017-12-20 07:10:20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":null,\"image_intro_caption\":null,\"image_intro_alt\":null,\"image_fulltext\":null,\"image_fulltext_caption\":null,\"image_fulltext_alt\":null}','{}','{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"sunfw_article_type\":\"standard\",\"sunfw_featured_image\":\"\",\"sunfw_audio_embed_code\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_title\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_url\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_text\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_author\":\"\",\"sunfw_video_url\":\"\"}',10,7,'','',1,1818,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(145,502,'Regulated Industries','regulated-industries','<div class=\"iccc-article-title\">\r\n<h3>Industry and Entity Regulation</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"main\" style=\"overflow: auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"iccc-figure-common\">\r\n<p><img class=\"iccc-figure-common-scaled\" src=\"images/iccc/photogalleries/RID.jpg\" alt=\"Regulatory Industry Divisional Staff - Head Office\" /></p>\r\n<p>Regulatory Industry Divisional Staff - Head Office</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<p>The Regulated Industries Division is responsible for regulating infrastructure and service sectors in Papua New Guinea under Part III of the Independent Consumer and Competition Commission Act 2002. Under this Part the Treasury Minister declared the following entities for regulation.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>PNG Power Limited</li>\r\n<li>PNG Ports Corporation Limited</li>\r\n<li>Post PNG Limited</li>\r\n<li>Motor Vehicle Insurance Limited</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In particular, the Commission directly regulates the above state-owned entities that operate in the industries as outlined.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The Electricity Supply Industry</li>\r\n<li>The Essential Ports Services Industry</li>\r\n<li>Postal Services Industry</li>\r\n<li>The Compulsory Third Party Motor Vehicles Insurance services industry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The regulated industries are declared under the respective industry Acts such as the Electricity Industry Act (Chapter No. 78), Harbours Act (Chapter No. 240), Postal Services Act 1996 and Motor Vehicles (Third Party Insurance) Act (Chapter No. 295).</p>\r\n<p>The regulatory frameworks administered by the Commission in regulating the above state-owned entities and the industries in which they operate are contained within a number of pieces of legislation, industry Codes of Practice and regulatory instruments known as “regulatory contracts”.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','',1,96,'2017-12-20 10:03:48',560,'','2018-01-27 01:04:51',560,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2017-12-20 10:03:48','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{}','{}','{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"sunfw_article_type\":\"standard\",\"sunfw_featured_image\":\"\",\"sunfw_audio_embed_code\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_title\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_url\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_text\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_author\":\"\",\"sunfw_video_url\":\"\"}',3,4,'','',1,2040,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(146,506,'Competition','competition','<div class=\"iccc-article-title\">\r\n<h3>Competition</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"main\" style=\"overflow: auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"iccc-figure-common\">\r\n<p><img class=\"iccc-figure-common-scaled\" src=\"images/iccc/photogalleries/CMFTD.jpg\" alt=\"Competition Management &amp; Free Trade Division Staff - Head Office\" /></p>\r\n<p>Competition Management &amp; Free Trade Division Staff - Head Office</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<p>The division enforces the competition provisions under Part VI of the ICCC Act which promotes economic efficiency which leads to lower prices, increased choices and greater economic growth and ultimately enhancement of the overall welfare of all Papua New Guineans.</p>\r\n<p>The ICCC’s work in the area of Competition is provided for under the Part VI of the Independent Consumer and Competition Commission Act 2002 (the ICCC Act). The enforcement of Part VI of the ICCC Act promotes economic efficiency which leads to business innovations, better quality, lower prices, increased choices for goods and services and greater economic growth and ultimately enhancement of the overall welfare of all Papua New Guineans.</p>\r\n<p>The ICCC performs enforcement and adjudication role to promote and secure competition process in the Papua New Guinean market. The objectives of its work in the area of enforcement of competition law (Part VI of the ICCC Act) are to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>promote and encourage fair trading practices and a fair market;</li>\r\n<li>facilitate effective competition and promote competitive market conduct;</li>\r\n<li>prevent the abuse of market power; promote and encourage the efficient operation of industries and efficient investment in industries;</li>\r\n<li>promote and protect the bona fide interests of consumers in relation to the acquisition and supply of goods and service.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Tobacco Products Proposed Amendments</strong></p>\r\n<p>{loadmodule mod_docman_documents,Tobacco Products Proposed Amendment Documents}</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','',1,99,'2017-12-20 11:51:20',560,'','2018-01-27 23:28:22',560,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2017-12-20 11:51:20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{}','{}','{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"sunfw_article_type\":\"standard\",\"sunfw_featured_image\":\"\",\"sunfw_audio_embed_code\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_title\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_url\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_text\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_author\":\"\",\"sunfw_video_url\":\"\"}',7,3,'','',1,1613,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(147,507,'Consumer Protection','consumer-protection','<div class=\"iccc-article-title\">\r\n<h3>Consumer Protection</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"mainbody\" style=\"overflow: auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"iccc-figure-common\">\r\n<p><img class=\"iccc-figure-common-scaled\" src=\"images/iccc/photogalleries/CPD.jpg\" alt=\"Consumer Protection Division Staff - Head Office\" /></p>\r\n<p>Consumer Protection Divisional Staff - Head Office</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Primary Functions</h4>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<p>The ICCC, through its Consumer Protection Division, strives to protect and promote the rights and interests of the consumers of Papua New Guinea.</p>\r\n<p>Consumer protection’s role is to advocate on behalf of consumers and protect their rights and interests. In consumer protection, the key functions of the Commission are:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n<li>To formulate and submit to the Minister policies in the interest of consumers,</li>\r\n<li>To consider and examine and where necessary, advise the Minister on the consolidation or updating of legislation providing protection to the consumer in the areas of public health, trade and commerce, motor vehicles and motor vehicle insurance, price surveillance and control, services and such other areas as may be required, and</li>\r\n<li>To liaise with other Departments and other government agencies in matters relating to consumer protection legislation</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Other Functions include:</h4>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Creating awareness and promoting consumer rights and interests in accordance with the provisions of law,</li>\r\n<li>Conducting investigations and taking appropriate action in relation to potential breaches of the consumer protection law,</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring consumer product safety by conducting market surveys and monitoring international developments,</li>\r\n<li>Issuing warning notices on potentially unsafe goods, developing consumer product and information standards and introducing ‘interim’ bans and permanent bans on unsafe or potentially unsafe goods,</li>\r\n<li>Conducting product recalls on unsafe goods,</li>\r\n<li>Conduct marketplace surveys on pricing on declared goods and services and that the appropriate service standards are followed,</li>\r\n<li>Undertaking checks, inspections of various weighting and measuring instruments used by the relevant industries (such as manufacturing, wholesaling and retailing, service, etc.) and,</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring the market place to ensure correct pricing of fuel and regulated services and the appropriate service standards are followed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>These functions are broadly reflected in the Divisions main areas of operations which are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Resolving and or assisting complaints, enquiries and problems involving misrepresentations in commercial advertising or unfair advertising,</li>\r\n<li>Assisting consumer who have purchased shoddy goods or goods that do not perform the functions that traders claim they do or goods that do not correspond with claims on the packaging,</li>\r\n<li>Removing unsafe or potentially unsafe consumer goods from the market or alerting consumers potential dangers relating to unsafe consumer goods</li>\r\n<li>Ensuring measuring apparatus are accurate, and</li>\r\n<li>Coordinating the Commission’s consultation and education program.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Supply of Shoddy Goods</h4>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<p>The Commission encourages consumers and small business to inform it of complaints, concerns or problems with goods they may have purchased or services with which they have been provided. In some cases the Commission will contact the trader complained of or in other cases it will provide an outline of a letter that a consumer may use to write to the trader.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">What should consumers do?</h4>\r\n<div class=\"iccc-article-text-content\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Consumers may contact the Commission on its toll free number  <span class=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i><i class=\"fa fa-volume-control-phone fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i></span> 180 3333, or</li>\r\n<li>They may call at any of the offices shown on the contact us page, or</li>\r\n<li>They may use the information provided in our complaints enquiry page to write to the trader or speak with the trader, or</li>\r\n<li>They may complete the online complaint/enquiry <span class=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i><i class=\"fa fa-wpforms fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i></span><a href=\"index.php/contact-us/complaint-or-enquiry\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Form</strong></a> and submitting it to the Commission.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','',1,98,'2017-12-20 11:51:48',560,'','2018-01-27 01:17:00',560,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2017-12-20 11:51:48','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{}','{}','{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"sunfw_article_type\":\"standard\",\"sunfw_featured_image\":\"\",\"sunfw_audio_embed_code\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_title\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_url\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_text\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_author\":\"\",\"sunfw_video_url\":\"\"}',10,9,'','',1,2132,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(148,510,'Our Priorities','our-priorities','<div class=\"iccc-article-title\">\r\n<h3>Our Priorities</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<!---BEGIN - GOAL CONTENT-->\r\n<h3 class=\"iccc-article-goal\">GOAL 1: PROMOTE COMPETITION AND REMEDY MARKET FAILURE</h3>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Strategies</h4>\r\n<div style=\"overflow-x: auto;\">\r\n<table class=\"iccc-article-goal-table\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1.1</td>\r\n<td>Develop new competition provision for the ICCC Act with a particular focus to make pre-merger notification mandatory in order to prevent changes in market structures that substantially lessen competition in the markets.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1.2</td>\r\n<td>Develop new merger review and authorization processes and systems to improve our efficiency and provide clear guidance to merger parties, authorization applicants and market participants.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1.3</td>\r\n<td>Introduce a Leniency Program to encourage and protect whistle blowers to inform the Commission about their anti-competitive dealings and arrangements with competing business.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1.4</td>\r\n<td>Identify highly concentrated industries and undertake targeted market studies with the aim to introduce competition.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1.5</td>\r\n<td>Investigate potential anti-competitive arrangements and behavior and take corrective measures consistent with the ICCC Act and or actions through the Courts.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1.6</td>\r\n<td>Expand and strengthen working relationship with international competition and authorities and bodies.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<!---END- GOAL CONTENT-->\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<!---BEGIN - GOAL CONTENT-->\r\n<h3 class=\"iccc-article-goal\">GOAL 2: EFFECTIVELY REGULATE DECLARED ENTITIES, INDUSTRIES AND PRICES OF GOODS AND SERVICES</h3>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Strategies</h4>\r\n<div style=\"overflow-x: auto;\">\r\n<table class=\"iccc-article-goal-table\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2.1</td>\r\n<td>Initiate productivity reviews into highly concentrated and efficient industries with the aim to establish the level of competition (if any) and recommend appropriate form of regulation based on international best practice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2.2</td>\r\n<td>Effectively monitor key price determinants in the global and regional markets that impact on the Commission\'s price determination of regulated goods and services.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2.3</td>\r\n<td>Respond to Government\'s request to undertake reviews into industries in highly concentrated and new deregulated markets with a view to provide Government with practical recommendation for evidence based policy options.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2.4</td>\r\n<td>Conduct timely reviews of regulated entities\' regulatory contracts and price orders with a view to ensure efficiency gains are passed on to business and consumers and prices of utilities are fair and just.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2.5</td>\r\n<td>Identify and develop appropriate regulatory tools such as standards, codes and regulations to foster competitive markets and promote consumer interest in concentrated markets.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2.6</td>\r\n<td>Proactively monitor and enforce price orders, licensing, technical and minimum service standards requirements in regulated entities to ensure compliance of regulatory contracts and ICCC price determinations.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<!---END- GOAL CONTENT-->\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<!---BEGIN - GOAL CONTENT-->\r\n<h3 class=\"iccc-article-goal\">GOAL 3: PROTECT THE SAFETY AND INTERESTS OF CONSUMERS</h3>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Strategies</h4>\r\n<div style=\"overflow-x: auto;\">\r\n<table class=\"iccc-article-goal-table\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3.1</td>\r\n<td>Improve our work practices to enable us to deliver results consistent with our consumer protection and enforcement initiatives and consumer protection best practice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3.2</td>\r\n<td>Undertake an active program of strong and managed partnerships with a broad range of domestic stakeholders that can assist us deliver outcomes that impact favorably on consumer welfare.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3.3</td>\r\n<td>Build relationships with international regulatory agencies to leverage their experience in our consumer protection and enforcement activities.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3.4</td>\r\n<td>Identify and implement regional consumer product safety enforcement approaches to minimize the risk of injury and death form hazards in consumer products.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3.5</td>\r\n<td>Undertake timely inspection of consumer protection issues and investigation into consumer complaints to ensure redress on behalf of consumers or take corrective measures consistent with the ICCC Act or actions through the Courts.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<!---END- GOAL CONTENT-->\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<!---BEGIN - GOAL CONTENT-->\r\n<h3 class=\"iccc-article-goal\">GOAL 4: INCREASE OUR LEGAL AND ADMINISTRATION EFFECTIVENESS</h3>\r\n<h4 class=\"iccc-article-sub-title\">Strategies</h4>\r\n<div style=\"overflow-x: auto;\">\r\n<table class=\"iccc-article-goal-table\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>4.1</td>\r\n<td>Strengthen our legal and financial administration services to increase our capability to effectively support our core business of promoting and safeguarding competition, protecting consumers\' interest and regulating declared industries, entities and goods and services.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>4.2</td>\r\n<td>Develop our financial, human resource administration and legal capabilities, knowledge and network through well trained and resourced staff.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>4.3</td>\r\n<td>Develop our precedence in case management, litigations and effective management of contracts (Retainer Agreements) when outsourcing cases to external firms.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>4.4</td>\r\n<td>Manage our finances effectively and maintain our commitment as a prudently managed and compliant agent of PNG laws.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>4.5</td>\r\n<td>Monitor the relevance and effectiveness of our laws and recommend appropriate changes consistent with international best practice to ensure these are responsive to our country\'s developing need; to enhance competition for the benefit of consumers.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>4.6</td>\r\n<td>Invest in operational systems, processes, management of Service Agreements and human resources to enhance our professionalism, capabilities and confidence to effectively and efficiently do our work.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<!---END- GOAL CONTENT-->','',1,95,'2017-12-22 20:53:07',560,'','2017-12-23 10:29:49',560,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2017-12-22 20:53:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{}','{}','{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"sunfw_article_type\":\"standard\",\"sunfw_featured_image\":\"\",\"sunfw_audio_embed_code\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_title\":\"\",\"sunfw_link_url\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_text\":\"\",\"sunfw_quote_author\":\"\",\"sunfw_video_url\":\"\"}',42,4,'','',1,1717,'{\"robots\":\"\"